      • register

        public java.lang.String register(java.lang.String username,
                                 java.lang.String fullName,
                                 java.lang.String password,
                                 java.lang.String confirmPassword)
        Register controls the flow of the user registration action. First, several validations are run on the user's input (e.g. if username is already taken, if username is not alphanumeric, if user password and confirmation do not match). When the user object passes all validations, it is saved to disk and will feedback to the user that their account has been created. Otherwise, an error message will be returned, informing the user what their error was.
        Parameters:
        username - the username
        fullName - the full name
        password - the password
        confirmPassword - the password confirmation
        Returns:
        the result
